  <title>Smart Attendance system using RFID</title>
<subsection xml:id="subsec-Introduction-attendance">
  <title>Introduction</title>
  <p>
    Attendance system is the evaluation system to monitor whether they are inside the organizations or not. It works based on the Radio Frequency. The RFID sensor receives the frequencies of the RFID tag, sensor will match the unique ID (represents the person) given for each tag.  It used EMF to automatically identify and track the tag. RFID consists of three parts a radio receiver to receive the frequency, tiny radio transponder receives the radio signal and emits a different radio signal and a transmitter to transmit radio waves. Application of RFID tag is widely used around the world. One of the applications of RFID tag is also used in forest to monitor the activities of wild animals.  In 2018 Government of Tamil Nadu introduces this scheme to monitor the attendance of the students. It captures the value of the card when passes through it. Higher officials can monitor from anywhere in the world.
  </p>
    <image source="/images/smart_attendance.jpg" width="40%"/>
</subsection>
