  <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-RFID-Sensor">
    <title>RFID Sensor</title>
    <p>
      RFID is an acronym for Radio Frequency Identification. It uses electromagnetic field to identify the object. It consists of a radio receiver, transmitter and tiny radio transponder. It is based on MFRC522 controller. The module will support 12C, SPI, UART. The RFID sensor has a sensor, a small key chain and a blank card to transmit and receive radio waves. RFID has 8 pins SDA, SCK, MOSI, MISO, IRQ, GND, RST and VCC.
    </p>
    <figure>
      <image source="/images/RFID_Sensor.jpg" width="40%"/>
      <caption>RFID Sensor</caption>
    </figure>
    <p>
      The table 4.4.2.2 explains each pin and its usage. Fig 4.4.2.2 displays the RFID.
    </p>
    <table>
